contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|puppy}} '''Puppy''' may refer to: * A pup, being the young of a [[dog]], other canine or some other animal species (such as seals) * By analogy, a young, relatively immature human (boy or girl), especially when considered inexperienced and/or conceited; as in [[puppy pile]] * [[Puppy Linux]], a Live CD Linux distribution * "[[The Puppy Episode]]," an 1997 episode of the TV sitcom ''[[Ellen (TV series)|Ellen]]'' in which Ellen DeGeneres' character comes out of the closet * [[Puppy (album)|''Puppy'' (album)]], an album by the band Fluke * ''[[We Can Only Live Today (Puppy)|Puppy]]'', a song by Belgian [[drum and bass]] producer [[Netsky (musician)|Netsky]] * [[Puppy (film)|''Puppy'' (film)]], Australian film * ''Puppy'', a sculpture created by [[Jeff Koons]] * [[The Puppies]], a 1990s rap group {{disambig}}
